The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring September 10, 2015, as World Suicide Prevention Day. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of mental health support and the prevention of suicide. It highlights the relationship between suicide and mental health conditions, such as depression and substance use disorders. The proclamation encourages Americans to promote mental well-being, recognize signs of mental health issues, and ask for help when needed. It also mentions the Affordable Care Act, which extends mental health and substance use disorder benefits to millions of Americans. The Clay Hunt Suicide Prevention for American Veterans Act and other efforts to support veterans' mental health are also mentioned. The proclamation emphasizes the responsibility of all people in suicide prevention and calls for raising awareness of mental health resources and support services.